model.name: InfoSec
model.documentation:
Information Security Model using Archi and Archimate
This model is currently the property of Ron Parker scmunk@secretchipmunk.com @scmunk 2018

element.name: Analytics
element.documentation: Systematic evaluation and examination of data

element.name: Compute
element.documentation: Computer-based calculation exposed through logical or physical means, can be extremely specialized services

element.name: Database
element.documentation: A collection of data containers and maintenance types

element.name: Developer
element.documentation: Set of abilities or services that can be used directly by the developer

element.name: Integration
element.documentation: Combining or incorporating processes and information from multiple entities

element.name: Intelligence
element.documentation: Subset of artificial intelligence that deals with voice, image, and language processing

element.name: IoT
element.documentation: Internet of Things, services that support distributed internet connected devices

element.name: Mobile
element.documentation: Services support the management and application development for mobile devices

element.name: Network and Delivery
element.documentation: Network related services

element.name: Management and Ops
element.documentation: Directing and maintaining runtime processing of people, resources, and processes

element.name: Security
element.documentation: General services to provide integrity, availability, and confidentiality

element.name: Storage
element.documentation: Services to maintain, accessed, and back up data

element.name: Relational
element.documentation: A database where the main elements being managed are tables/rows and ways those objects are connected

element.name: Key-Value
element.documentation: A database where the main element being managed is a collection of paired data items

element.name: Document
element.documentation: A database where the main element being managed is document oriented

element.name: Cache
element.documentation: Ability to hold and distribute transactional data to increase performance or reduce backend processing

element.name: Migration
element.documentation: Movement of data from one management platform, environment, or technology to another

element.name: Virtual Servers
element.documentation: Compute processing provided using software

element.name: Containers
element.documentation: Specialized form of virtualization that allows for ease of deployment and scaling

element.name: Orchestration
element.documentation: Automated coordination of multiple tasks potentially across domains or platforms

element.name: Serverless
element.documentation: Functional level processing is implemented without direct ties to platform, or hardware

element.name: Batch Processing
element.documentation: Performing a series of collected operation as a group

element.name: Object
element.documentation: A database where the main element being managed is a object, whether binary or in some other format

element.name: Backup
element.documentation: To logically or physically map a copy of data in its current state

element.name: Disk
element.documentation: Storage optimized for physical or virtual compute devices (hard drives)

element.name: Archiving
element.documentation: Moving data to a less frequently accessed position, or medium

element.name: Bulk
element.documentation: Large dataset transfer or handling, may use specialized hardware or media

element.name: Disaster Recovery
element.documentation: Storage used for restoration of business services after a disaster event

element.name: Virtual
element.documentation: Network or network subset based on configuration or software2

element.name: DNS
element.documentation: Domain Name Services, a directory and system for locating resources by name or address

element.name: CDN
element.documentation: Content Delivery Network, large scale distribution or global distribution of video, files, or static web content

element.name: Load Balancing
element.documentation: Infrastructure service to distribute processing across resources, may also be used to provide availability of resources

element.name: Dedicated
element.documentation: A communication path set aside for a single purpose or by single users

element.name: VPN
element.documentation: Virtual Private Network, cryptographically secured communication between two points over a public network4

element.name: Data Warehouse
element.documentation: A large source of data collection from many sources

element.name: MapReduce
element.documentation: Large scale and parallel application of data processing and analytics

element.name: Analytics
element.documentation: Systematic evaluation and examination of data

element.name: Visualization
element.documentation: Analyzing results through sight, using diagrams, pictures, or graphics

element.name: Search
element.documentation: Highly scalable searching using artificial intelligence/machine learning to provide better results

element.name: Machine Learning
element.documentation: A subset of artificial Intelligence that deals with learning through repetition or exposure

element.name: Virtual Assistant
element.documentation: Determining context, language, and interpretation of vocal requests using artificial intelligence or machine learning

element.name: Speech
element.documentation: Services to interpret speech process it using compute resources

element.name: Visual
element.documentation: Identifying or interpreting images through the use of a subset of artificial intelligence

element.name: Edge Computing
element.documentation: The ability to extend computing service to the device

element.name: Streaming
element.documentation: High volume event collection and processing from a large number of distributed devices

element.name: IoT Dev
element.documentation: Specific development processes for IoT devices

element.name: Monitoring
element.documentation: Observing the qualities of key resources and taking actions on those qualities if necessary

element.name: Deployment
element.documentation: Managed installation or transfer of data or a system

element.name: Compliance
element.documentation: The determination and statement of how well directives are being followed.

element.name: Configuration
element.documentation: Inventory and determination of operational settings applied to hardware or software

element.name: Development
element.documentation: Tools and services for rapid creation of mobile applications

element.name: Testing
element.documentation: Methodologies and tools to test implementation for functional and non-functional requirements

element.name: Management
element.documentation: Directing configuration and use of mobile devices

element.name: Analytics
element.documentation: Systematic evaluation and examination of data

element.name: Authentication
element.documentation: Positive identification of the claim that an entity is who they state they are.

element.name: Authorization
element.documentation: Determining if an entity has the requesting right to an action for a resource; if they have permission.

element.name: Data Protection
element.documentation: Protection processes and technologies for data at rest, data in transit, and data being processed.

element.name: Encryption
element.documentation: Set of services to provide integrity, and confidentiality to data

element.name: Directory
element.documentation: Database that may contain identities, or users and related

element.name: Capability
element.documentation: Undefined

element.name: Firewall/IPS
element.documentation: Detection and prevention of traffic flow based on packets info, protocol, address, and rules

element.name: Capability
element.documentation: Undefined

element.name: Email
element.documentation: E-mail services that can be readily used by developers

element.name: Messaging
element.documentation: Communication and event handling tools that can be integrated with applications and systems

element.name: Workflow
element.documentation: Connecting multiple steps or processes together to complete a larger unit of work

element.name: API Management
element.documentation: Registration, deployment, scaling, and security for APIs

element.name: Testing
element.documentation: Methodologies and tools to test implementation for functional and non-functional requirements

element.name: Building
element.documentation: Process that drive creating and testing solutions for eventual deployment

element.name: Capability
element.documentation: Undefined

element.name: CyberSecurity
element.documentation: Information security protection and assurance.

element.name: Boundary
element.documentation: Security that defines and protects an area and the entry to that area

element.name: Firewall
element.documentation: Detection and prevention of traffic flow based on packets info, protocol, address, and rules

element.name: VPN
element.documentation: Virtual Private Network, cryptographically secured communication between two points over a public network4

element.name: NAC
element.documentation: Network Access Control, rules based authentication and authorization for devices on a network

element.name: Proxy
element.documentation: An agent or function that sits in front of an entity and represents it adding functionality to the represented entity

element.name: Content Control
element.documentation: Analysis of files, or containers whether at rest or in motion for presence of malicious intent.

element.name: Anti-Virus / Malware
element.documentation: Inspecting content to determine if an executable has malicious intent directly or indirectly by modifying local systems.

element.name: Anti-Spam
element.documentation: Inspecting content, and sites to determine if they promote or contain unwanted or unsolicited e-mails or requests.

element.name: Data Protection
element.documentation: Protection processes and technologies for data at rest, data in transit, and data being processed.

element.name: DLP
element.documentation: Data Loss and Prevention (or protection), system or process to monitor and protect unauthorized data from the protected areas

element.name: Listing and Filtering
element.documentation: Whitelisting or blacklisting resources, or limiting resources based on rules

element.name: Detection
element.documentation: Determine or identify the occurrence of a cybersecurity event

element.name: NIDS/NIPS
element.documentation: Network Intrusion Protection and Prevention

element.name: HIDS/HIPS
element.documentation: Host-based intrusion detection and/or protection system

element.name: Anomaly Detection
element.documentation: Analyzing behavior and patterns to determine if any action or events falls outside of what is normally expected.

element.name: Security Event Management
element.documentation: A centralized system for determining and reacting to security events

element.name: Logging
element.documentation: Tracking and maintaining data over a period of time, event tracking

element.name: WIDS
element.documentation: Wireless Intrusion Detection, malicious intent detection for wireless communication

element.name: Threat and Vulnerability
element.documentation: People, processes, and technology to identify, detect, and respond to exposure or potential exposure

element.name: Vulnerability
element.documentation: Processes and technologies to detect, remedy, or prevent exposure to being harmed

element.name: Compliance Monitoring
element.documentation: Inventory and check for proper software and hardware including configuration.

element.name: Forensics
element.documentation: Process of controlled information collection criminal evidence

element.name: Mobile Device Management
element.documentation: Hardware, software, and device management including configuration, control, and inventory

element.name: Research/Intell
element.documentation: Gathering and applying information to reduce or prevent security events

element.name: Patching
element.documentation: Updating software or operating systems to remove vulnerabilities or reduce their likelihood

element.name: Identity and Access
element.documentation: Identity and Access Capability

element.name: Access Admin
element.documentation: Life-cycle maintenance of identities and permissions.

element.name: Entitlement
element.documentation: Authorizations or permissions assigned to an entity

element.name: Identity
element.documentation: Electronic record representing an entity that is used for authentication and authorization

element.name: Provisioning
element.documentation: Creating accounts, authorizations, assigning permissions and resources based on workflows and rules

element.name: Administration
element.documentation: The definition, creation, and maintenance of security models, groups, roles, and other access control constructs.

element.name: Directory
element.documentation: Database that may contain identities, or users and related

element.name: Synchronization
element.documentation: Keeping the changes the same for entities across multiple IAM repositories

element.name: Access Control
element.documentation: Runtime aspects of authentication, federation, and authorization.

element.name: Authorization
element.documentation: Determining if an entity has the requesting right to an action for a resource; if they have permission.

element.name: Authentication
element.documentation: Positive identification of the claim that an entity is who they state they are.

element.name: Federation
element.documentation: Use a trust between parties to provide authentication and authorization

element.name: Adaptive Risk
element.documentation: The ability to determine assurance levels or risk levels at runtime then adjust to levels.

element.name: SSO
element.documentation: Single Sign On, session based authentication that can span multiple systems without further interaction from the user

element.name: IAM Governance
element.documentation: Process of directing and controlling IAM services

element.name: IAM Forensics
element.documentation: Process of controlled information collection criminal evidence in the IAM space

element.name: Privileged Access
element.documentation: Management of people and processes that have higher than normal permissions

element.name: Access Certification
element.documentation: Determining if the permissions granted to an entity are valid and follow directives such as Least Privilege.

element.name: Cloud Access
element.documentation: Determining and monitoring usage of cloud services along with the associated access control.

element.name: Cryptography
element.documentation: General methods to protect data integrity or confidentiality.

element.name: Encryption
element.documentation: Set of services to provide integrity, and confidentiality to data

element.name: PKI
element.documentation: Public Key Infrastructure

element.name: Digital Signatures
element.documentation: Service to provide a method for authenticity and integrity for messages or digital documents

element.name: Rights Management
element.documentation: Protection of digital materials using cryptographic controls

element.name: Key Management
element.documentation: Cryptographic secret management including symmetric and asymmetric keys

element.name: Compliance
element.documentation: The determination and statement of how well directives are being followed.

element.name: Privacy
element.documentation: Keeping data, mainly an individuals, from unauthorized access

element.name: BC/DR
element.documentation: Business Continuity and Disaster Recovery.

element.name: Governance
element.documentation: Process of directing and controlling security services

element.name: Assurance
element.documentation: The program, processes, or technologies that provide the required level of security related confidence.

element.name: Incident
element.documentation: A malicious or suspicious event

element.name: Training/Awareness
element.documentation: Horizontal education that is sometimes mandatory

element.name: Policy
element.documentation: A directive driving behavior supported by management, can be administrative or technical

element.name: Strategy
element.documentation: Creating a plan for individual areas or departments to meet overall goals or objectives
